Years in the French West Indies\" (1890)\n\nBULLET::::- Lafcadio Hearn Memorial Museum\nBULLET::::- Goryo Hamaguchi\n\nBULLET::::- Amenomori, Nobushige (1905). \"Lafcadio Hearn, the Man,\" \"The Atlantic Monthly\", October 1905.\nBULLET::::- Bisland, Elizabeth (1906). \"The Life and Letters of Lafcadio Hearn\", Vol. II, New York: Houghton, Mifflin & Company.\nBULLET::::- Dawson, Carl (1992). \"Lafcadio Hearn and the Vision of Japan\", Johns Hopkins University Press.\nBULLET::::- Hirakawa, Sukehiro and Yoko Makino (2018), \"What is Shintō? Japan, a Country of Gods, as Seen by Lafcadio Hearn\", Tokyo: Kinseisha.\nBULLET::::- Kunst, Arthur E. (1969). \"Lafcadio Hearn\", Twayne Publishers.\nBULLET::::- Langton, D. H. (1912). \"Lafcadio Hearn: Journalist and Writer on Japan,\" \"The Manchester Quarterly\", Vol. XXXI.\nBULLET::::- Mais, S. P. B. (1920). \"Lafcadio Hearn.\" In \"Books and their Writers\", Grant Richards, Ltd.\nBULLET::::- McWilliams, Vera (1946). \"Lafcadio Hearn\", Houghton Mifflin Company.\nBULLET::::- Miner, Earl Roy (1958). \"The Japanese Tradition in British and American Literature\", Princeton University Press.\nBULLET::::- Monaham, Michael (1922). \"Lafcadio Hearn,\" \"An Attic Dreamer\", Mitchell Kennerley.\nBULLET::::- More, Paul Elmer (1905). \"Lafcadio Hearn.\" In \"Shelburne Essays\", Second Series, G. P. Putnam's Sons.\nBULLET::::- Noguchi, Yone (1905). \"Lafcadio Hearn, A Dreamer,\" \"National Magazine\", Vol. XXII, No. 1.\nBULLET::::- .\nBULLET::::- ; republished in .\nBULLET::::- Setsu, Koizumi (1918). \"Reminiscences of Lafcadio Hearn\", Houghton Mifflin Company.\nBULLET::::- Thomas, Edward (1912). \"Lafcadio Hearn\", Houghton Mifflin Company.\n\nBULLET::::- Lafcadio Hearn Memorial Museum Matsue city in Japan\nBULLET::::- Lafcadio Hearn Gardens Tramore in Ireland\nBULLET::::- Hearn's Works, by T Russel\nBULLET::::- Works by Lafcadio Hearn, at Unz.org\nBULLET::::- Works by Lafcadio Hearn, at Hathi Trust\nBULLET::::- Hearn's influence in lit